main event: A witness observed a white oval-shaped object that changed in appearance, changed direction, and increased in size over Cedarville, Ohio.
interesting points: The object had a reddish glow.
The object was observed for about 1 1/2 minutes at a distance of 800 feet.
The report notes that very little information regarding the sighting was obtained and details of the observation or investigation were not recorded.
The report concluded that there was insufficient information to determine if the object was a known phenomenon or not.
The witness was asked a series of detailed questions about the sighting, including the weather conditions, their location, and the object's movement and appearance.
